<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-341] All references to &apos;poollist&apos; in the Lustre manual should be replaced with &apos;pool_list&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-341</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&apos;lfs poollist&apos; no longer works in master (2.8.53) and was replaced by &apos;lfs pool_list&apos;. Thus, the Lustre manual should be updated to reflect this change. There are four references to &apos;poolist&apos; in the manual:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;32.1.1. Synopsis&lt;br/&gt;
32.1.3. Options&lt;br/&gt;
32.1.4. Examples (twice)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-59&quot; title=&quot;poollist is the accepted usage of pool_list.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-59&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-59&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1364&quot; title=&quot;lfs &amp;#39;poollist&amp;#39; is incorrectly recognised as &amp;#39;pool_list&amp;#39; by lfs, the lfs manpage and the Manual.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1364&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1364&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for thoughts on which form of pool list to use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
